PLANT PROFILE | 'Zanzibar Gem' or 'ZZ Plant' (zamioculcas zamiifolia). Known around the traps as the 'plant that thrives on neglect' this tough specimen is a great all rounder and is a perfect choice for people starting out with houseplants. It also makes a great gift option for the same reason (no one should be gifted a needy plant)! Light: This plant can tolerate medium light conditions but will grow better in filtered light.
Water: Sparingly, allowing the soil to dry out almost completely between waterings. Sometimes this can be up to and around once a month!
Note: Keep its glossy leaves dust-free with regular wipe downs, they love the dust otherwise. photo: @selenabrownson .
